## Process
1. Start from `design-system-context-routing.mdc` (always-on router) to select only required rules.
2. Use tokens from `design-system-tokens.mdc` when exact values/aliases are required.
3. Theme via `data-theme` on `<html>`: `light` (default) or `dark`.
4. Load only the relevant component/layout rule files below for the current task.
5. If a token is missing, request it—do not invent.

## Token usage
- **CSS**: Define variables in `globals.css` or theme file; consume via `var(--token-name)`.
- **Tailwind**: Use arbitrary values, e.g. `bg-[var(--bg-base-default)]`, `text-[var(--text-base-default)]`.
- **Inline**: Prefer `style={{ color: 'var(--text-brand-default)' }}` over hex literals.
- **Only** use tokens defined in `design-system-tokens.mdc`; all tokens are derived from Figma.

